<subSubSection id="6AFD6538AA2BFFF0B4DCFB608DF7FB2A" pageId="1" pageNumber="230" type="description">
<paragraph id="225836B3AA2BFFF0B4DCFB608DF7FB2A" blockId="1.[136,1452,1216,2071]" pageId="1" pageNumber="230">
Differing from 
<taxonomicName id="E5E74D30AA2BFFF0B56EFB608D2EFB0E" box="[314,620,1216,1242]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Trypetheliaceae" genus="Astrothelium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Trypetheliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="230" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="amylosporum">
<emphasis id="1093EAA1AA2BFFF0B56EFB608D2EFB0E" box="[314,620,1216,1242]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="230">Astrothelium amylosporum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having 4 ascospores per ascus, in the smaller ascospores, and in the ascomata being mostly covered by a thallus layer.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6AFD6538AA2BFFF0B4E9FAA88EAEFA92" pageId="1" pageNumber="230" type="etymology">
