<paragraph id="225836B3AA2BFFF0B4E9FA1C8E87F95E" blockId="1.[136,1452,1216,2071]" pageId="1" pageNumber="230">
Thallus corticolous, distinctly corticate, olive-green to pale green, smooth to uneven. Ascomata solitary to somewhat aggregate but not pseudostromatic, with apical, separate ostioles, 
<quantity id="E51F9B56AA2BFFF0B05EFA408BC2FA2F" box="[1034,1152,1504,1531]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="230" unit="mm" value="1.15" valueMax="1.3" valueMin="1.0">1–1.3 mm</quantity>
diam, erumpent, covered by thallus except for the broad, dark ostiolar area surrounded by a thin, irregular whitish rim, darkening when dry. Hamathecium inspersed. Ascospores 4 per ascus, muriform, with 9–11 transverse and 3–4 longitudinal septa per segment, with the distinct diamond-shaped lumina and with a pronounced median septum, ellipsoid to fusiform, 100– 110 × 24–30 µm, IKI+ blue.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="225836B3AA2BFFF0B4E9F9348A7EF97B" blockId="1.[136,1452,1216,2071]" box="[189,1340,1684,1711]" pageId="1" pageNumber="230">
<emphasis id="1093EAA1AA2BFFF0B4E9F9348E07F97A" bold="true" box="[189,325,1684,1710]" pageId="1" pageNumber="230">Chemistry:</emphasis>
Secondary substances absent; thallus surface UV-, K-, medulla K-; ascomata surface UV-.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="225836B3AA2BFFF3B4E9F9188EFBFEB9" blockId="1.[136,1452,1216,2071]" lastBlockId="2.[136,1452,158,365]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="231" pageId="1" pageNumber="230">
Amyloid ascospores are comparatively rare in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="E5E74D30AA2BFFF0B761F9188BB5F907" authority="(Aptroot &amp; Lucking 2016)" baseAuthorityName="Aptroot &amp; Lucking" baseAuthorityYear="2016" box="[821,1271,1720,1747]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Trypetheliaceae" genus="Astrothelium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Trypetheliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="230" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1093EAA1AA2BFFF0B761F9188C87F906" box="[821,965,1720,1746]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="230">Astrothelium</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="46764B42AA2BFFF0B787F9188BB2F907" author="Aptroot, A. &amp; Lucking, R." box="[979,1264,1720,1747]" pageId="1" pageNumber="230" pagination="763 - 982" refId="ref2588" refString="Aptroot, A. &amp; Lucking, R. (2016) A revisionary synopsis of the Trypetheliaceae (Ascomycota: Trypetheliales). Lichenologist 48: 763 - 982. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0024282916000487" type="journal article" year="2016">Aptroot &amp; Lücking 2016</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Among species with muriform ascospores and lacking secondary compounds, the most similar is 
<taxonomicName id="E5E74D30AA2BFFF0B04BF97C8AE5F922" authority="Flakus &amp; Aptroot" authorityName="Flakus &amp; Aptroot" box="[1055,1447,1756,1782]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Trypetheliaceae" genus="Astrothelium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Trypetheliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="230" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="amylosporum">
<emphasis id="1093EAA1AA2BFFF0B04BF97C8B95F922" box="[1055,1239,1756,1782]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="230">A. amylosporum</emphasis>
Flakus &amp; Aptroot
</taxonomicName>
, which differs by its larger ascospores (125–170 ×27–40 µm) occurring in numbers of 8 per ascus and in the fully exposed, brown-black ascomata (( 
<bibRefCitation id="46764B42AA2BFFF0B5F5F8848D34F8EB" author="Flakus, A. &amp; Kukwa, M. &amp; Aptroot, A." box="[417,630,1828,1855]" pageId="1" pageNumber="230" pagination="661 - 692" refId="ref2899" refString="Flakus, A., Kukwa, M. &amp; Aptroot, A. (2016) Trypetheliaceae of Bolivia: an updated checklist with descriptions of twenty-four new species. The Lichenologist 48: 661 - 692. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0024282915000559" type="journal article" year="2016">
Flakus 
<emphasis id="1093EAA1AA2BFFF0B5A2F8858D72F8EA" box="[502,560,1828,1854]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="230">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="E5E74D30AA2BFFF0B6DEF8848B15F8EA" authority="Flakus &amp; Aptroot" authorityName="Flakus &amp; Aptroot" box="[650,1111,1828,1854]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Trypetheliaceae" genus="Astrothelium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Trypetheliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="230" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="bullatum">
<emphasis id="1093EAA1AA2BFFF0B6DEF8848CC5F8EA" box="[650,903,1828,1854]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="230">Astrothelium bullatum</emphasis>
Flakus &amp; Aptroot
</taxonomicName>
forms lateral ostioles and the ascomata are fully immersed between bullate thallus portions (
<bibRefCitation id="46764B42AA2BFFF0B718F8E88B5CF8B7" author="Flakus, A. &amp; Kukwa, M. &amp; Aptroot, A." box="[844,1054,1864,1891]" pageId="1" pageNumber="230" pagination="661 - 692" refId="ref2899" refString="Flakus, A., Kukwa, M. &amp; Aptroot, A. (2016) Trypetheliaceae of Bolivia: an updated checklist with descriptions of twenty-four new species. The Lichenologist 48: 661 - 692. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0024282915000559" type="journal article" year="2016">
Flakus 
<emphasis id="1093EAA1AA2BFFF0B7F4F8E98C9BF8B6" box="[928,985,1864,1890]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="230">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="E5E74D30AA2BFFF0B065F8E88E22F852" authority="Sipman &amp; Aptroot" authorityName="Sipman &amp; Aptroot" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Trypetheliaceae" genus="Astrothelium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Trypetheliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="230" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="palaeoexostemmatis">
<emphasis id="1093EAA1AA2BFFF0B065F8E88AE9F8B6" box="[1073,1451,1864,1890]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="230">Astrothelium palaeoexostemmatis</emphasis>
Sipman &amp; Aptroot
</taxonomicName>
is overall similar to the new species, including ascospore size, but the ascospores are richly muriform, with numerous small cells and thin septa and walls, not displaying diamond-shaped lumina (
<bibRefCitation id="46764B42AA2BFFF0B146F8308F87F81A" author="Aptroot, A. &amp; Sipman, H. J. M. &amp; Barreto, F. M. O. &amp; Nunes, A. D. &amp; da Silva Caceres, M. E." pageId="1" pageNumber="230" pagination="27 - 43" refId="ref2630" refString="Aptroot, A., Sipman, H. J. M., Barreto, F. M. O., Nunes, A. D. &amp; da Silva Caceres, M. E. (2019) Ten new species and 34 new country records of Trypetheliaceae. The Lichenologist 51: 27 - 43. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 002428291800052 X" type="journal article" year="2019">
Aptroot 
<emphasis id="1093EAA1AA2BFFF0B127F8318AEEF87E" box="[1395,1452,1936,1962]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="230">et al.</emphasis>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
). Both 
<taxonomicName id="E5E74D30AA2BFFF0B541F8148DFAF81A" authority="Aptroot &amp; M. Caceres" authorityName="Aptroot &amp; M. Caceres" box="[277,696,1972,1999]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Trypetheliaceae" genus="Astrothelium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Trypetheliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="230" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="flavoduplex">
<emphasis id="1093EAA1AA2BFFF0B541F8148EF5F81A" box="[277,439,1972,1998]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="230">A. flavoduplex</emphasis>
Aptroot &amp; M. Cáceres
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="E5E74D30AA2BFFF0B6BAF8148BFAF81A" authority="Aptroot &amp; M. Caceres" authorityName="Aptroot &amp; M. Caceres" box="[750,1208,1972,1999]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Trypetheliaceae" genus="Astrothelium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Trypetheliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="230" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="ochroleucoides">
<emphasis id="1093EAA1AA2BFFF0B6BAF8148CF5F81A" box="[750,951,1972,1998]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="230">A. ochroleucoides</emphasis>
Aptroot &amp; M. Cáceres
</taxonomicName>
deviate by producing lichexanthone (
<collectionCode id="44F6AE76AA2BFFF0B562F8788E22F826" box="[310,352,2008,2034]" country="Colombia" name="Departamento de Biologia de la Universidad del Valle" pageId="1" pageNumber="230">UV</collectionCode>
+ yellow); 
<taxonomicName id="E5E74D30AA2BFFF0B5B4F8788DC7F826" box="[480,645,2008,2034]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Trypetheliaceae" genus="Astrothelium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Trypetheliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="230" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="flavoduplex">
<emphasis id="1093EAA1AA2BFFF0B5B4F8788DC7F826" box="[480,645,2008,2034]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="230">A. flavoduplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs further in the strongly pseudostromatic ascomata covered with yellow-orange pigment and the longer ascospores (110–350 × 20–27 µm), whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="E5E74D30AA2BFFF0B010F85C8A4EF7C2" box="[1092,1292,2044,2070]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Trypetheliaceae" genus="Astrothelium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Trypetheliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="230" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="ochroleucoides">
<emphasis id="1093EAA1AA2BFFF0B010F85C8A4EF7C2" box="[1092,1292,2044,2070]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="230">A. ochroleucoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which agrees with 
<taxonomicName id="E5E74D30AA28FFF3B4EBFF3F8ECBFF6C" box="[191,393,158,185]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Trypetheliaceae" genus="Astrothelium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Trypetheliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="231" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="mordonialensis">
<emphasis id="1093EAA1AA28FFF3B4EBFF3F8ECBFF6C" box="[191,393,158,185]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="231">A. mordonialensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in ascospore number and size (80–115 × 15–24 µm), the pseudostromatic ascomata are exposed and brown-black (
<bibRefCitation id="46764B42AA28FFF3B505FF628D25FF09" author="Aptroot, A. &amp; Caceres, M. E. S. &amp; Johnston, M. K. &amp; Lucking, R." box="[337,615,194,221]" pageId="2" pageNumber="231" pagination="983 - 994" refId="ref2519" refString="Aptroot, A., Caceres, M. E. S., Johnston, M. K. &amp; Lucking, R. (2016) How diverse is the lichenized fungal family Trypetheliaceae (Ascomycota: Dothideomycetes)? A quantitative prediction of global species richness. The Lichenologist 48: 983 - 994. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0024282916000463" type="journal article" year="2016">Aptroot &amp; Cáceres 2016</bibRefCitation>
). Two similar species, but with non-amyloid ascospores, are 
<taxonomicName id="E5E74D30AA28FFF3B150FF638EC8FED4" authority="Aptroot &amp; M. Caceres" authorityName="Aptroot &amp; M. Caceres" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Trypetheliaceae" genus="Astrothelium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Trypetheliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="231" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="tetrasporum">
<emphasis id="1093EAA1AA28FFF3B150FF638AE9FF08" box="[1284,1451,195,221]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="231">A. tetrasporum</emphasis>
Aptroot &amp; M. Cáceres
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="E5E74D30AA28FFF3B590FF478B09FED4" authority="(Makhija &amp; Patw.) Aptroot &amp; Lucking" authorityName="Aptroot &amp; Lucking" baseAuthorityName="Makhija &amp; Patw." box="[452,1099,230,257]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Trypetheliaceae" genus="Astrothelium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Trypetheliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="231" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="alboverrucum">
<emphasis id="1093EAA1AA28FFF3B590FF478DC1FED4" box="[452,643,230,257]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="231">A. alboverrucum</emphasis>
(Makhija &amp; Patw.) Aptroot &amp; Lücking
</taxonomicName>
: the first has larger ascospores (145–175 × 30–35 µm), bullate thallus, and ascomata covered by thallus except the protruding ostiole, whereas the former specie also has larger ascospores (85–170 × 23–33 µm) and its ascomata are hemispherical with a whitish cover (
<bibRefCitation id="46764B42AA28FFF3B4DBFEF28EECFEB9" author="Aptroot, A. &amp; Lucking, R." box="[143,430,338,365]" pageId="2" pageNumber="231" pagination="763 - 982" refId="ref2588" refString="Aptroot, A. &amp; Lucking, R. (2016) A revisionary synopsis of the Trypetheliaceae (Ascomycota: Trypetheliales). Lichenologist 48: 763 - 982. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0024282916000487" type="journal article" year="2016">Aptroot &amp; Lücking 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
